===2000 census===
At the 2000 [[census]],<ref name="GR2" /> there were 711 people, 250 households and 182 families living in the CDP. The [[population density]] was 2,287.7/km{{sup|2}} (6,010.7/mi<sup>2</sup>). There were 268 housing units at an average density of 862.3/km{{sup|2}} (2,265.7/mi<sup>2</sup>). The racial makeup of the CDP was 87.34% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]] (55.8% were [[Non-Hispanic White]]),<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.muninetguide.com/states/florida/municipality/Gun_Club_Estates.php |title=Demographics of Gun Club Estates, FL |publisher=MuniNetGuide.com |access-date=9 December 2007}}</ref> 2.25% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.14% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.14% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 3.52% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 6.61% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 39.80% of the population.

In 2000, there were 250 households, of which 34.8% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 45.2% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 17.2% had a female householder with no husband present, and 26.8% were non-families. 17.2% of all households were made up of individuals, and 5.2% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.84 and the average family size was 3.09.

In 2000, 26.2% of the population were under the age of 18, 9.3% from 18 to 24, 36.0% from 25 to 44, 21.2% from 45 to 64, and 7.3% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 34 years. For every 100 females, there were 108.5 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 105.9 males.

In 2000, the [[median household income]] was $33,380, and the median family income was $28,375. Males had a median income of $19,943 compared with $21,372 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the CDP was $12,560. None of the families and 3.7% of the population were living below the [[poverty line]], including no under eighteens and none of those over 64.

As of 2000, [[English language|English]] was the [[first language]] for 53.50% of all residents, while [[Spanish language|Spanish]] was the [[mother tongue]] for 46.49% of the population.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mla.org/map_data_results&state_id=12&county_id=&mode=place&zip=&place_id=28305&cty_id=&ll=&a=&ea=&order=r |title=MLA Data Center Results for Gun Club Estates, Florida |publisher=[[Modern Language Association]] |access-date=9 December 2007}}</ref>

